{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Url Encode Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Url Encode Filter</h1>

<p>URL-encodes a string, making it safe for use in query parameters.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ value | url_encode }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "hello world" | url_encode }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> hello+world</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "foo=bar&baz=qux" | url_encode }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> foo%3Dbar%26baz%3Dqux</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "user@example.com" | url_encode }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> user%40example.com</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p>Uses Go's <code>url.QueryEscape</code>, which encodes spaces as <code>+</code> (query string encoding). Special characters such as <code>=</code>, <code>&amp;</code>, <code>?</code>, <code>@</code>, and <code>/</code> are percent-encoded.</p>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/url_decode">url_decode</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
